						<div class="postbody">Thank you Kasumi and Tokumaru.<br /><br />I've started the next portion of the game that I am working on. In continuing with branches and comparisons I've come across this statement in the tutorial that I'm working with which is confusing to me. Since we are already talking about it I thought I would bring it up. This is for adding two numbers.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent"><br />AddOnes:<br />&nbsp; LDA onesDigit&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; load the lowest digit of the number<br />&nbsp; CLC <br />&nbsp; ADC onesAdd&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; add new number, no carry<br />&nbsp; STA onesDigit<br />&nbsp; CMP #$0A&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; check if digit went above 9. If accumulator &gt;= $0A, carry is set<br />&nbsp; BCC AddTens&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; if carry is clear, all done with ones digit<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; carry was set, so we need to handle wrapping<br />&nbsp; LDA onesDigit<br />&nbsp; SEC<br />&nbsp; SBC #$0A&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; subtract off what doesnt fit in 1 digit<br />&nbsp; STA onesDigit&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; then store the rest<br />&nbsp; INC tensDigit&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; increment the tens digit<br /><br />&nbsp; AddTens:<br /><br /></div><br /><br />You'll notice in the Add Ones portion of the code, he compares the number in the accumulator to #$0A (Decimal Ten) and then uses a BCC statement (branch if accumulator is less than ten) to the ad tens portion of the code. Shouldn't this be a BCS statement (branch to ad tens if acumulator is greater than or equal to ten)?<br /><br />He then goes on to load the digit into the accumulator prior to the digit being larger than ten and stubtracts ten from it and stores the value as the ones digit. This makes no sense to me. Lets say for instance, if the number in the accumulator is 7 and you subtract ten from it. You would then have -3 in as your ones digit in your score?<br /><br />EDIT: I just realized I misunderstood how I was reading this and I now realize how this works. Sorry, been staring at code to long tonight and my brain sort of glitched out. Sorry. Again though thank you for all your help guys. I know it can be hard to work with beginners at times <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

