						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If you do need to keep the accumulator, you can just add another branch to handle the case where the numbers are equal:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda #$20<br />cmp #$20<br />beq Equal<br />bcs GreaterThan<br />Equal:</div><br /></div><br /><br />If you are able, instead of loading a variable into the accumulator and comparing it to a constant (or another variable) and doing a double branch to find 'greater than' you can do the reverse and use less than.<br /><br />&quot;Normal&quot; way:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda foo<br />cmp #$20<br />beq skip<br />bcs GreaterThan<br />skip:</div><br /><br />Alternative method:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda #$20<br />cmp foo<br />bcc GreaterThan<br /></div></div>

