						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">mysteriousity wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">AddOnes:<br />&nbsp; LDA onesDigit&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; load the lowest digit of the number<br />&nbsp; CLC <br />&nbsp; ADC onesAdd&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; add new number, no carry<br />&nbsp; STA onesDigit<br />&nbsp; CMP #$0A&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; check if digit went above 9. If accumulator &gt;= $0A, carry is set<br />&nbsp; BCC AddTens&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; if carry is clear, all done with ones digit<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; carry was set, so we need to handle wrapping<br />&nbsp; LDA onesDigit<br />&nbsp; SEC<br />&nbsp; SBC #$0A&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; subtract off what doesnt fit in 1 digit<br />&nbsp; STA onesDigit&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; then store the rest<br />&nbsp; INC tensDigit&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; increment the tens digit<br /><br />&nbsp; AddTens:</div></div><br />This can be optimized a lot... Look at this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;clc<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda OnesDigit<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;adc OnesAdd<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta OnesDigit<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sbc #9<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bcc OnesDone<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta OnesDigit<br />OnesDone:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda TensDigit<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;adc TensAdd<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta TensDigit<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sbc #9<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bcc TensDone<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta TensDigit<br />TensDone:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;(...)</div><br />You can compare AND adjust the digit at the same time with SBC #9 (since the carry is clear, it will actually subtract 10), and use the result of the comparison to decide between ignoring the adjusted value or using it. The adjusted value is only used when the carry is set, so the next digit will be incremented automatically (no need for INC, and no need to CLC before each ADC).<br /><br />I know you are probably not worried about optimizations like this yet, but I wanted to show that assembly doesn't have to be so strict, that you can often combine operations and make use of the status flags in non-obvious ways.<br /><br />I couldn't make subtraction as classy, because the status of the carry flag have to be manually adjusted for the next digit, but it's still better than the straightforward way:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;sec<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda OnesDigit<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sbc OnesSub<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bcs SkipFixOnes<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;adc #10<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;clc<br />SkipFixOnes:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta OnesDigit<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda TensDigit<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sbc TensSub<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bcs SkipFixTens<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;adc #10<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;clc<br />SkipFixTens:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta TensDigit<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;(...)</div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
