			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If I'm comparing to a constant, instead of doing this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda Value<br />cmp #8<br />beq label&nbsp; &nbsp;;Branch if Value = 8<br />bcc label&nbsp; &nbsp;;Branch if Value &lt; 8<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;;End result is branching if Value &lt;= 8<br /></div><br /><br />I do this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda Value<br />cmp #9<br />bcc label&nbsp; &nbsp;;Branch if Value &lt; 9<br /></div><br /><br />I think Kasumi may have mentioned doing a similar trick with comparing variables (subtract one from one of the variables before comparing), but it works better with constants. Not entirely related, but I figured I'd mention it as a cycle-saving trick.</div>

